Detailed Description

cvmx_mio_uart::_far

The FIFO access register is used to enable a FIFO-access mode for testing, so that the receive FIFO can be written by software and the transmit FIFO can be read by software when the FIFOs are enabled. When FIFOs are not enabled it allows the MIO_UART(0..1)_RBR to be written by software and the MIO_UART(0..1)_THR to be read by software. Note, that when the FIFO-access mode is enabled/disabled, the control portion of the receive FIFO and transmit FIFO is reset and the FIFOs are treated as empty.
